    "created_at": "2026-02-16T13:49:30Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-02-16T13:49:30Z",
    "body": "Today I tried to compile Starship on my 64-bit Debian GNU/Hurd system, and the systemstat crate failed again, for the same reason as the day I opened the issue: it couldn't find the definition `target_os = \"hurd\"` in the crate.\r\n\r\nThen I cloned the latest version of the systemstat crate, available at https://github.com/valpackett/systemstat, which is the one Starship uses, onto my system, and it gave the same error, which is to be expected. The latest version of systemstat is 0.2.5, which is the same version number Starship was using the day I opened the issue. It's expected that if systemstat adds something like support for a specific operating system, it will jump to a version like 0.2.6 or at least 0.2.5.1.\r\n\r\nWhat is the basis for writing \"systemstat appears to have added support for hurd.\"? Where did you get that information?\r\n\r\nThank you so much for looking into this issue.\r\n\r\nRegards.\r\nJose Luis.\r\n\r\n\r\nEl domingo, 15 de febrero de 2026, 19:37:20 CET David Knaack, ***@***.***> escribió:\r\ndavidkna left a comment (starship/starship#7148)\r\n\r\nsystemstat appears to have added support for hurd.\r\n\r\n—\r\nReply to this email directly, view it on GitHub, or unsubscribe.\r\nYou are receiving this because you authored the thread.Message ID: ***@***.***>\r\n",
